<subSubSection id="9FB3D084061E23791B9A1E4FFD2FC036" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D716830F061E23791B9A1E4FFD2FC036" blockId="4.[166,1225,591,778]" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">
<bibRefCitation id="B338FEFE061E23791B9A1E4FFE01C155" author="Sakenin, H. &amp; Samin, N. &amp; Rastegar, J. &amp; Havaskary, M. &amp; Imani, S. &amp; Linnavuori, R. E." box="[219,450,591,618]" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" pagination="861 - 872" refId="ref2958" refString="Sakenin, H., Samin, N., Rastegar, J., Havaskary, M., Imani, S. &amp; Linnavuori, R. E. 2010. A faunistic survey on Heteroptera (Insecta) of Western Iran. Linzer Biologische Beitrage, 42, 861 - 872." type="journal article" year="2010">Sakenin et al.(2010)</bibRefCitation>
claimed that 
<taxonomicName id="10A9F88C061E237919181E4FFC84C156" authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1887" box="[601,839,591,617]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Brachycoleus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decolor">
<emphasis id="E5DD5F1D061E237919181E4FFC84C156" box="[601,839,591,617]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">Brachycoleus decolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
along with133 other species were collected from west of 
<collectingCountry id="AFBEC39F061E23791AF71E70FE29C1B5" box="[438,490,624,650]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">Iran</collectingCountry>
, surprisingly in a completely similar work 
<bibRefCitation id="B338FEFE061E237918A81E6FFB0BC1B5" author="Samin, N. &amp; Sakenin, H. &amp; Linnavuori, R. &amp; Havaskary, M. &amp; Mohebbi, H. R." box="[1001,1224,623,650]" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref3013" refString="Samin, N., Sakenin, H., Linnavuori, R., Havaskary, M., Mohebbi, H. R. 2011. A faunistic survey of Heteroptera (Insecta) from western Iran. Calodema, 146, 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="2011">Samin et al. (2011)</bibRefCitation>
reported and published mostly same species in a vanity fake journal named &quot;Calodema&quot; (
<bibRefCitation id="B338FEFE061E23791BEE1EAFFEA4C1F5" author="Tin, L. &amp; Ivana, B. &amp; Biljana, B. &amp; Ljubica, I. B. &amp; Dragan, M. &amp; Dusan, S." box="[175,359,687,714]" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" pagination="69 - 81" refId="ref3130" refString="Tin, L., Ivana, B., Biljana, B., Ljubica, I. B., Dragan, M., &amp; Dusan, S. 2014. Predatory and fake scientific journals / publishers - a global outbreak with rising trend: a review. Geographica Pannonica, 18 (3), 69 - 81." type="journal article" year="2014">Tin et al., 2014</bibRefCitation>
). Also no depository has been stated in both papers for the collected and identified specimens. Therefore the validity of these reports is in doubt as it is unclear if vouchers were deposited for further examination.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9FB3D084061E23791B9A1F28FE78C04C" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" type="description">
<paragraph id="D716830F061E23791B9A1F28FE78C04C" blockId="4.[166,1225,808,883]" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">
I thank Dr. Rauno E. Linnavuori (Saukkokuja 10, FIN-2122 Raisio, 
<collectingCountry id="AFBEC39F061E237918C41F28FC12C001" box="[901,977,808,830]" name="Finland" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">Finland</collectingCountry>
) for confirmation of the species identification and providing materials for insect collection at the Natural History Museum of University of Guilan, used in this study.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
